Two ssh methods to save your energy
I highly recommend using the methods in both link to save your time!

ssh-keygen will save the process of typing login passwords
Check these websites 
(https://www.thegeekstuff.com/2008/11/3-steps-to-perform-ssh-login-without-password-using-ssh-keygen-ssh-copy-id/)
(https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/set-up-personal-ssh-keys-on-macos/)

.ssh/config will save the process of typing passwords when syncing files!
Note that this method will also save two-factor authentication!
Check this website 
(https://hcc.unl.edu/docs/connecting/reusing_ssh_connections_in_linux_or_mac/) 

